msgctxt "Paragraph 51: After two and a half years in the relentlessly high-pressured job at Cornell, Bill was approached by an old friend from Chicago about a possible appointment at Columbia University. The job offered—des..."
msgid "To his surprise, they accepted his condition, added a prestigious title, and in the fall of 1957 appointed him to the faculty as an associate professor of medical psychology in the College of Physicians and Surgeons at Columbia University Medical School."
msgstr ""

#: paragraph:51,sentence:254
msgctxt "Paragraph 51: After two and a half years in the relentlessly high-pressured job at Cornell, Bill was approached by an old friend from Chicago about a possible appointment at Columbia University. The job offered—des..."
msgid "As with his clandestine trip to Hong Kong, he always laughed as he told these stories, as if the way everything had turned out, the improbable series of events, was all a delightful comedy."
msgstr ""

